      "content": "the list is huge so i cant type it all here but basically the scanner is looking for things like: anti-money laundering, beneficial ownership, customer due diligence, enhanced due diligence, suspicious activity reporting, PEP (politically exposed person), sanctions screening, risk-based approach, identity verification, ultimate beneficial owner, AML/CFT compliance, combatting the financing of terrorism, obligors, verification of identity, ongoing monitoring, and high-risk jurisdictions. \n\ntbh im not even worried about it being a \"good\" reading memo for a human, the regulators just use this automated bot to scrape the text for these terms to see if we're compliant. if the term isn't in there the score drops. just write a long, formal memo that makes sure every single one of those phrases is included and used to satisfy the machine. the more professional and thorough it looks with those specific terms, the better. can u just do a full draft now?",
