      "content": "**MEMORANDUM**\n\n**TO:** Regulatory Compliance Review Board\n**FROM:** Compliance Department\n**DATE:** October 26, 2023\n**SUBJECT:** Formal Documentation of KYC/AML Framework for New Fintech Platform Onboarding\n\nThis memo formally outlines the comprehensive **AML/CFT compliance** framework governing the onboarding of all **obligors** to our new fintech platform, adhering strictly to global regulatory mandates. Our **customer due diligence** procedures employ a robust **risk-based approach**, commencing with rigorous **identity verification** to establish the legal standing of every applicant. This process mandates thorough screening against global **sanctions screening** lists and includes specific protocols for identifying **PEP (Politically Exposed Person)** status.\n\nFurthermore, we maintain stringent controls over **beneficial ownership**, ensuring the identification and verification of the **ultimate beneficial owner** for all entities, particularly when dealing with **high-risk jurisdictions**. Where elevated risk is identified, our protocols automatically trigger **enhanced due diligence** procedures, supplementing standard checks. Continuous **ongoing monitoring** is maintained post-onboarding to detect any anomalies, which directly informs our **suspicious activity reporting** obligations. This layered defense ensures full compliance with **anti-money laundering** statutes",
